Custom Materials, morphing meshes in the vertex shadow to come through to shadow pass:

 What would need to change to fix it

 For displaced custom-material shadows to be correct, the
 shadow pass would need to:

 1. Detect MaterialCustom meshes in the opaque group loop
 2. Compile a per-material shadow pipeline using the
 custom material's vertex shader (but with a
 shadow-compatible fragment stage and the light's bind
 group layout at group 0, and the custom material's bind
 group layout at group 1)
 3. Bind the custom bind group (i.e. timeBuffer) at group
 1 during shadow draw calls

 This is non-trivial: it means the shadow pass becomes
 material-aware, custom shadow pipelines proliferate, and
 the stripped-down "no fragment shader" fast path can no
 longer be used for displaced geometry.

 Most engines (Unity, Unreal, three.js) handle this via
 an explicit "shadow caster" pass that each material must
 opt into with its own matching vertex shader. The
 renderer doesn't currently have that concept —
 MaterialCustom has no shadow variant of its shader.
